
Context and problem
  Enable an application to handle transient failures when it tries to connect to a service or network resource, by transparently retrying a failed operation.
  This can improve the stability of the application.
  For example, a database service that's processing a large number of concurrent requests can implement a throttling strategy that temporarily rejects any further requests until its workload has eased.
  An application trying to access the database might fail to connect, but if it tries again after a delay it might succeed.

Solution
  If an application finds a request to a service is failure, it can handle failure in below ways.
